    The Biofire Respiratory Panel v2.1 assay is a PCR-based assay that enables detection of respiratory pathogens from patient samples. This test was approved by the Food and Drug Administration (FDA) for testing of nasopharyngeal swabs in viral transport media. Â This assay was further developed and its performance characteristics have been determined for testing lower respiratory specimens using this method by the Children's Health Dallas Laboratory.

    This test detects the presence of nucleic acid and does not assess organism viability. As a result, PCR should not be used as a test of cure. Negative results do not preclude respiratory pathogen infection and should not be used as the sole basis for diagnosis, treatment, or other management decisions.

The Biofire Respiratory Panel v2.1 assay is a PCR-based assay that enables detection of respiratory pathogens from patient samples. This test was approved by the Food and Drug Administration (FDA) for testing of nasopharyngeal swabs in viral transport media. Â This assay was further developed and its performance characteristics have been determined for testing lower respiratory specimens using this method by the Children's Health Dallas Laboratory.

This test detects the presence of nucleic acid and does not assess organism viability. As a result, PCR should not be used as a test of cure. Negative results do not preclude respiratory pathogen infection and should not be used as the sole basis for diagnosis, treatment, or other management decisions.
